    <item>
      <title>Comparing buffers with vimdiff</title>
      <description>&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Vim's diff mode allows us to easily compare the contents of two (or more) buffers. We can start Vim in diff mode using the &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;vimdiff&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; command, or if Vim is already running we can switch to diff mode using the &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;:diffthis&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; command. The beauty of the &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;:diffthis&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; command is that it works with unnamed buffers, whereas &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;vimdiff&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; can only work with files.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;

</description>
      <enclosure url="http://media.vimcasts.org/videos/60/vimdiff.m4v" length="13194774" type="video/x-m4v"/>
      <pubDate>Wed, 15 Jan 2014 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
      <guid>http://vimcasts.org/episodes/comparing-buffers-with-vimdiff/</guid>
      <link>http://vimcasts.org/episodes/comparing-buffers-with-vimdiff/</link>
