      <title>Registers: the Good, the Bad, and the Ugly Parts</title>
      <description>&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;To the newcomer, Vim's way of doing things may seem strange, but with familiarity it becomes natural. Many of Vim's features seemed odd to me at first, but when I got used to them I recognised that they had their own particular elegance. However, there's one feature of Vim that still feels awkward to me: using registers for copy and paste. The deeper my understanding of registers becomes, the more they frustrate me!&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;

</description>
      <pubDate>Mon, 25 Nov 2013 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
      <guid>http://vimcasts.org/blog/2013/11/registers-the-good-the-bad-and-the-ugly-parts/</guid>
