      <title>Evaluating scripts with Vim's expression register</title>
      <description>&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;In &amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;/e/56&amp;quot;&amp;gt;the previous lesson&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt; we learned how use the expression register to evaluate simple calculations. We can also call built-in and user-defined Vimscript functions, and thanks to the &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;system()&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; function, we can also fetch output from external scripts.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;

