      <title>Enhanced abbreviations with :Abolish</title>
      <description>&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Vim's built-in abbreviation feature is handy if you want to auto-correct words that you frequently misspell, but it requires a lot of setup. The &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;:Abolish&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; command makes it easy to generate abbreviations that will correct multiple forms of the same word.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;

&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;em&amp;gt;This is the final of a three-part series on Tim Pope’s &amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://github.com/tpope/vim-abolish&amp;quot;&amp;gt;abolish&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt; plugin.&amp;lt;/em&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;

