      <description>&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;The &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;:Subvert&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; command lets us create a particular style of regular expressions with ease. It's great for matching irregular singular and plural words in plain English and also for variable names that come in &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;snake_case&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; and &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;MixedCase&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; forms.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;

