      <title>VimGolf - Prime Numbers</title>
      <description>&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;For the VimGolf challenge &amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;http://vimgolf.com/challenges/4d1c27940e3d7832db000010&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;quot;List the first 100 prime numbers&amp;quot;&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;, there's a solution that uses a regular expression to detect prime numbers. At 43 keystokes, it's not the winning solution, but I think it's the most interesting one. It uses a few clever Vim tricks, including macros, control-a to increment, the very magic pattern switch, and the &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;:global&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; command. There's a lot to learn from those 43 keystrokes, so let's study it!&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;

